<title>USA: Automobile Protection to post charge.</title>
<headline>Automobile Protection to post charge.</headline>
<dateline>ATLANTA 1997-02-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>Automobile Protection Corp said Wednesday it will post a pre-tax charge in the range of $750,000 to $1 million related to its litigation against Everest Reinsurance Holdings Inc.</p>
<p>The company could not be reached for further comment. It did not say when it would be posting the charge.</p>
<p>The company said it had filed the complaint against Everest, contending it improperly denied claims on assumption of liability endorsements issued to its dealers in 1991.</p>
